<TITLE> 2 Jamaat men remanded over war crime charges </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rajshahi, Feb 14 (bdnews24.com) Police Saturday remanded in custody for two days the two Jamaat-e-Islami adherents, who were arrested Friday on war crime charges in Mohanpur Upazila. On Saturday, the arrestees were brought before the Rajshahi magistrate's court where S K Khodanewaz, sub-inspector for Mohanpur Police Station, asked for a five-day remand. Magistrate Muhammad Alamgir granted two-day remand and also asked for the arrest of the 17 others linked to the case. Officer in charge of Mohanpur Police Station Asaduzzaman Milon said Daud Hossain, 70, and Noor-e Anwar, 65, were picked up from their homes in Dyeing Para-Berabari area. It is the first instance in the country where alleged war criminals have been arrested in a regular case, said Shahabuddin Khan, superintendent of Rajshahi police. Mejarul Sheikh, a day-labourer, of Birsorail area under Shah Makhdum Police Station filed the case. Mejarul is the son of a martyred freedom fighter Bashir Uddin Sheikh, said Milon, the OC. "The arrestees confessed that they had joined collaborators' forces during the liberation war in 1971," Khan, the SP, told bdnews24.com. bdnews2
